Test Title: Verify export button opens export options
Steps:
1-Go to System Settings > Documentation Categories > List Documentation Categories
2-Click on export button
Description: Ensure that clicking on the Extract button displays export format options (PDF, XLS).
Preconditions:
1-User logged in
2-user in List Categories page

Steps:
1-Go to System Settings > Documentation Categories > List Documentation Categories
2-Click on export button
3-Choose PDF
Description: Check that the system generates a PDF file containing the same data displayed in the instruction list.
Preconditions:
1-User logged in
2-user in List Categories page
Expected Result: A PDF file should be downloaded showing the same data as the instruction list.
Actual Result: PDF file downloaded successfully and showed the same data in the categories list
Comments: PDF generated successfully, and data matched

Test Title: Verify that the search returns matching instructions
Steps:
1-Go to System Settings > Documentation Categories > List Documentation Categories
2-Type keyword in the search field
3-Click on Search button
Description: Validate that entering a keyword filters the instruction list and shows only matching records
Preconditions:
1-User logged in
2-user in List Categories page
Expected Result: Only categories containing the search keyword should be displayed in the list
Actual Result: Only categories containing the search keyword displayed successfully

Test Title: Verify that the selected record are permanently removed after confirming deletion
Steps:
1-Go to System Settings > Documentation Categories > List Documentation Categories
2-Click on the delete icon
3-Click yes in the confirmation pop-up
Description: Ensure that deleting record works correctly
Preconditions:
1-User logged in
2-user in List Categories page
Expected Result: The deleted record should be removed from the list
Actual Result: System deletes the selected record from the list

2-Click on delete icon
3-Click on cancel button
Description: Ensure that cancelling deletion works correctly
Preconditions:

Steps:
1-Go to System Settings > Documentation Categories > List Documentation Categories
2- Identify a Category that already has Sub Categories (e.g., “مواد خام”).
3- Click on the Sub Category button for that Category.
4- Observe the page that opens.
5- Check if displayed Sub Categories belong only to the selected Category.
Description: Verify that clicking the Sub Category button opens the Sub Category page and displays only the subcategories related to the selected parent category.
Preconditions:
1-User logged in
2-user in List Categories page
Expected Result: The system should open the Sub Category page and display ONLY the subcategories linked to the selected parent Category. Category name/title should also match the selected Category.
Actual Result: the sub category page opened and displayed sub catogories successfully
